<p>A.507/4/34.<br/>N.F.<br/>COMMONWEALTH OF AUSTRALIA.</p>
<p>DEPARTMENT OF DEFENCE<br/>MELBOURNE<br/>AUG 31 1917</p>
<p><u>No.63433</u></p>
<p>Dear Sir,<br/>I have to acknowledge receipt of your telegram of even date relative to your son, Lieut. K.A. Ferguson, 4 th Divisional Headquarters, and to state that it is officially reported that he is returning to Australia. A communication containing this information was sent to you on 6 th idem addressed "Supreme Court, Sydney." Information is now to hand stating he is on the Hospital Ship "Kanowna" which is due at Fremantle today. A <strike> letter</strike> lettergram or telegram addressed care of the ship should be delivered without difficulty.</p>
<p>Yours faithfully<br/>T.Trumble [indecipherable]<br/>A/SECRETARY.</p>
<p>Mr.Justice Ferguson,<br/>Menzies' Hotel,<br/><u>MELBOURNE</u></p>
<p>[Transcribed by Eric Hetherington for the State Library of New South Wales]</p>
